<p>
<seg id=1> While at the same time near China town in Indonician capital Jakarta, Chinese and local Indonian were guarding their houses together. </seg>
<seg id=2> Ever since the serious riot happened in May, China town was lashed by violence again. </seg>
<seg id=3> Please listen to another report by the VOA journalist Grant from Jakarta. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The nightfall and the soldiers fired their guns to warn and disperse the youngsters throwing stones from the area of China town. </seg>
<seg id=5> Several hours ago, thousands of people in crowds set on fire and burned a bank, which is less than a mile from the President's residence. Soon the fire spreaded to the neighboring shops </seg>
<seg id=6> This group of youngsters broke the door of the shop with a road lamppost. </seg>
<seg id=7> When beginning to attack the Chinese on Wednesday, a group of people pulled a Chinese onto the street, beat him, and threw him into a pitch. </seg>
<seg id=8> Later the soldiers drove a armoured carrier and saved the heavily wounded man. </seg>
<seg id=9> Tanks patrolled the streets covered with bricks and broken glasses, thousands of soldiers armed with gun and tear gas bullets were guarding the local commercial area, forbidding the thugs to draw near. </seg>
<seg id=10> Businessman running electronic products there had to move out after the riot in May. </seg>
<seg id=11> Reporter saw a 29 years old young man called Ming guarding behind the iron-wire barricades with only a short pant and a leather belt on. </seg>
<seg id=12> This young man who works in a computer company said that he and his neighbors who believe in Islam were guarding there all night long, preventing the thugs from robbing their families. </seg>
<seg id=13> Mr. Ming said that after the riot in May, his neighbor has already set up this iron-wire, but he did not expect to use it so quickly. </seg>
<seg id=14> In some places with barricades, residents expelled groups of strangers with big lumbers. </seg>
<seg id=15> A local resident called Daxiyat wore a Muslim hat and dressed in Muslim sarong. </seg>
<seg id=16> He told the reporter that most of these young thugs are coming from other places out of China town after they heard that riot has broken out here. </seg>
<seg id=17> Thugs had robbed and destroyed a metro-station one-mile away from here. When the soldiers were chasing at them, the threw away their shoes. Computers and clothes-racks were sreaded all the way. </seg>
